m/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/Thumbnails/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 1:03:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> Kimaya's someone who views plants and animals as &quot;family&quot; as much as she does just about everyone and everything she runs into.  It's a good thing she's comfortable with the idea that you honor things' place in the life/death cycle by &quot;putting all their gifts to good use&quot;, or she'd have died cold and starving at level 1.<br>
<br>
So yeah, she wears gnomeskin gloves and has kept the wood elf steak someone offered her once.  She just knows better than to TALK about it and tick folks off.  She may be many things, but she tries not to be impolite... *grin* <p><p align="center">
<img src="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/73377kimaya-sig.gif" width="381" height="100">
<br>
<a href="http://home.bellsouth.net/personalpages/PWP-TwilightBastion"><i>~ Click here to visit the Bastion ~</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 3:25:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> Nice and shiny armour.  Baka is never seen outside his armour.  The shinier the armour, the better.  He may rarely leave his armour behind in absolute dire emergencies (such as death) but still keeps some spare armour behind.<br>
<br>
Normal clothes..  Pah, no point.  He seriously doubts he'll ever be told to strip too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 4:19:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Nice and shiny armour. Baka is never seen outside his armour. The shinier the armour, the better. He may rarely leave his armour behind in absolute dire emergencies (such as death) but still keeps some spare armour behind.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That doesn't answer the question, silly.<br>
<br>
If you found a suit of &quot;Dull Aluminum&quot; armor that, when worn, looked very shiny, would you wear it?<br>
<br>
Conversely, if you found a suit of &quot;High Polished Radiantly Shiny&quot; armor that, when worn, just looked kinda like plain old platemail, would you still wear it?<br>
<br>
In other words, to what extent does the description of the item drive your roleplay view of it, to what extent does the way it looks when worn?  <br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 6:12:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> *sighs*  If it helps at all, I'm one of those people who likes a full suit of matching armour.  That's my personality at work.  Patchwork armour just doesn't feel right, unless there's some clear advantage to not wearing it.  You'll rarely see me outside of a full suit (I still don't feel right wearing a Netherbian Chitin, reminds me far too much of System Shock 2 *shudders*)<br>
<br>
In the end, I'm not sure of the preference between descriptive language and onscreen graphics.  Even Verant aren't stupid enough to make dull aluminium more shiny than radiantly shiny plate, but in the end, 99.9% of the RP on this server is done through text, so I guess the description would matter more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukloeviseq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KloevisEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 6:16:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.cci.clarku.edu/ebarry/pix1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> &quot;reminds me far too much of System Shock 2 *shudders*&quot;<br>
<br>
I still get nightmares from Shodan's creepy cackling....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
panting and sweating as you run through my corridors... <p><img src="http://web.cci.clarku.edu/ebarry/ban.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiobhanai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siobhanai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 6:17:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> I am a wood elf and a follower of Tunare.  I decided  I won't kill bears or wolves, nor would I wear armor made from their skin (unless you were able to assure me the leather or fur came from a wolf or bear who died of wholey natural causes).  But if the blood or skin used to make armor came from a bandit or other sentient being who decided to turn away from Tunare's blessings and prey on the weak and/or helpless (such as teh gnolls who infest the lands around Qeynos or the kobolds who prey upon the gnomes and Erudites), I would gladly wear it as a warning to others not to take such a path; I might even join in the taking of that life which has been turned to evil.<br>
<br>
However, if I found the blood or other body part was taken from an innocent or a follower of Tunare or other good dieties, then I would scowl at the wearer and not take such to wear myself.  Unless one wearing such were to give it up, I would class them in league with the evil that made it.<br>
<br>
Basically, I have more sympathy for unsentient creatures for they cannot chose right from wrong.  It is a creature that chooses evil that should be treated as an &quot;animal&quot; and even used for his flesh &amp; body parts.<br>
<br>
/ooc I am finding my character is a tad bit more bloodthirsty than I am in life... hmmmm... she is also a lot more fearless than I am or even than any of my other EQ characters have been, even the one who is the same race and class but higher level.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/02 6:41:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: fashion statement</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Even Verant aren't stupid enough to make dull aluminium more shiny than radiantly shiny plate<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I can think of several occasions when an item's graphic was way out of whack with it's description.  Rusty Rapiers used to have a longsword graphic.  Gauntlets of the black used to be silver.  Ornate chain looks exactly the same when worn as ringmail.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ETC.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
But that's besides the point.  It was an extreme (if silly) example to clarify the issue at hand to those who effectively answered the philosophical question of &quot;Does armor &amp; equipment in EQ carry an inherent roleplay value of more depth than the way it looks when worn?&quot; with &quot;I like leather pants!!  Especially on wood elf chix!!!&quot;.<br>
<br>
I know everyone has sets of armor they really like to wear.<br>
<br>
What I'm asking is, do you see gnomeskin armor as black leather, or the boiled flesh of gnomes?  Do you react accordingly?  If you're playing a paladin, would a shadowknight infuriate you even more if you saw him wearing a band of Rodcet Nife, or would you think to yourself &quot;Hmm, nice stats on that ring, I should get one too.&quot;<br>
<br>
- Syll<br>
<br>
PS: /sigh<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/30/02 8:31:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=28>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif width=68 height=146></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oops!</span><hr size=1> Shadowknights can't wear the Band of Rodcet Nife, but I see your point.<br>
<br>
Well, being in the evil camp, we PRIDE ourselves on wearing Flayed Skin, Gnome Skin, what not.  It fits well and Antoin claims his flayed skin bracer was made from beggars.  That shuts 'em up.<br>
<br>
Animal skins?  Slaughter!  Natural causes?  Disease Cloud...heh heh.<br>
<br>
The gnomeskin boots we found on the Raid of the Tower of Frozen Shadow turned out to be Maladominus' uncle, however.  That was a bit painful.<br>
<br>
((Antoin also changes his bracer graphics when he uses Dark Empathy.  Normally I let my Moktor Bracer (normal plate) show but when he slices his wrist and drips the blood on the one to be healed, he swaps to the Flayed Skin graphic (blood-soaked leather look.)))<br>
<br>
 <p>--Captain Antoin Nolouj
<br>Knight of the Dark Oceans
<br>League of Shadows</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usilenaeonfirionavie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silenae on FirionaVie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/30/02 11:44:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1805.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oops!</span><hr size=1> Actually, i see gnomeskin as skin ripped from corpses of those tiny bearded fellows, then tanned and sewn into a nice piece of armor. And i tend to react that way too, if i notice it. (Which, in this case might be &quot;ohh... nice. Did you skin them yourself ?&quot;) Now that said, i have not seen any Dark elf skin armor.. but if i did, i would definately offer the wearer a few carefully selected words.<br>
